name: Inner Workings
description:
The largest sphere can make contact with another object, and the smallest is always in contact with the biggest, which is the way the universe is made. We are all a part of the same orbit. Each time we have contact with something, whether it is a person or a book or a flower or a tree or the sky, it affects us in some way. This effect is the same for each of us. Each one of us is an individual but at the same time we are a part of the universe and we are all the same.
